<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1565" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1565">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/407.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Department has received a telegram from Chiarí, to the following
                            effect: “Constituted authorities, in league with largely increased body
                            of policemen armed with rifles, terrorize citizens, put them in jail
                            without any cause or trial, attack and even murder them. Personal
                            liberty and security do not exist. Complaints to governor have no
                            effect. American intervention should be extended to control police,
                            otherwise public peace may be disturbed at any moment.” Department has
                            replied: “The complaint contained in your telegram of yesterday would
                            seem to be a matter proper to be laid before the supervision
                            committee.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>